<TITLE> DU teacher quits over 'sexual scandal' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 1 (bdnews24.com)Professor Mohammed Afzal Hossain stepped down on Sunday as chairman of tourism and hospitality management department of Dhaka University over alleged sex scandal. He resigned after students of his department accused him with sexual harassment of a student. He sent in his resignation letter to the office of vice chancellor at around 4:30pm. DU vice chancellor AAMS Arefin Siddique told bdnews24.com that he received the resignation letter. Earlier professor Hossain told bdnews24.com, "A big gang is conspiring against me. I am quitting because I will not be able to finally survive in the face of the conspiracy." Recently, students of the department staged protest rallies and held news conference demanding resignation of the chairman on charges of sexual harassment. Professor Hossain became chairman on May 10, 2009. bdnews24.c
